HEADWORD: LF
<hw>LF</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Electronics)</fld> <def>Low frequency, a
term used to refer to radio waves of a frequency from 30 to 300
kilohertz. Contrasted to <contr>HF</contr>, high frequency.</def>
<mark>[Acronym]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> low frequency.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

